<paragraph id="FF6D36A0FFA07A08FF48FA54FD5FAD79" blockId="2.[151,1437,1511,2005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<bibRefCitation id="9B434B51FFA07A08FF48FA54FEB9AD14" author="Nielson" box="[151,320,1511,1536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1982) A revision of the subfamily Coelidiinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) IV. Tribe Coelidiini. Pacific Insects Monograph, 38, 1 - 318." type="journal article" year="1982">Nielson (1982)</bibRefCitation>
adequately described and illustrated this species. The following additional features are noted. Male pygofer with dorsal marginal sclerotized process distally lobe-like with anterior margin of lobe crenulated (
<figureCitation id="67E92A25FFA07A08FAB0F9BFFF4FAD5C" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 52" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1716,1739]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,432,1697]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,419,1713]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 52. Speceis of Mahellus. 48. Chaetotaxy of forefemur of M. distanti; 49. Chaetotaxy of metabasitarsus and second tarsomete of M. distanti, ventral view; 50 – 52. Posterior portion of male pygofer of Mahellus, dorsal view showing dorsal marginal sclerotized process: 50. M. cardoni sp. nov.; 51. M. distanti; 52. M. ungulatus sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569771/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
). Female similar to male with ovipositor projecting much beyond pygofer. Sternite VII and first and second pair of valvulae as described in generic description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
